Product information

Pros and cons

According to our dryer expert

  • Your clothes stay in good condition for longer, because the AbsoluteCare system adjusts the drying temperature and rotation speed to every type of laundry.
  • The SensiDry technology dries your laundry at a low temperature, which saves energy and protects your clothes.
  • You can connect your dryer to your washing machine with SyncDry, and adjust the dryer cycle to the most recent wash cycle.
  • The dryer doesn't have SmartDry to choose a faster drying time or lower energy consumption.
  • The dryer doesn't have the AbsoluteCare Plus system to evenly dry your laundry and to keep the fabric soft for longer.

Description

You can keep your favorite clothes in good condition for longer with the AEG TR86CBC87 dryer. With an 8kg load capacity, you have space for small and medium-sized loads of laundry. For example, the bedding of a double bed or a few outfits. The AbsoluteCare system adjusts the cycle and drum movements to the type of fabric in the drum. This way, your favorite sweater retains its shape and your clothes don't shrink. Don't want to sort your clothes. Choose the MixDry cycle. Via the app, you can easily turn the dryer on remotely and choose extra cycles. With a B energy label, you can dry all your clothes very energy-efficient. That saves you on your energy bill.

Tips for using this product

Insure your dryer

Receive more coverage in case of damage than with your standard warranty. Coolblue takes care of everything: from taking out the insurance to repairs. Is a repair not possible? You receive the purchase price as CoolblueCredit.

What am I insured for?

  • Fall and impact damage
  • Water damage
  • Manufacturing defects outside the warranty

What am I not insured for?

  • Damage you deliberately cause
  • Damage that doesn't affect the product functioning (such as scratches)
  • Damage due to gross negligence

XCover insurace

XCover is allowed to arrange and process insurances on behalf of the insurer. The insurances are governed by Belgium law. If you have a complaint, you can contact the or our customer service .

Read more about insurance

How do I insure my dryer?

First, add your dryer to your shopping cart. On the next page, choose the Protection Plan below. You always have a 30-day return window and pay no deductible in case of damage.

XCover Protection without theft cover
  • 5-year advance payment
    143,- one-time payment (28,60 per year)
  • 4-year advance payment
    99,- one-time payment (24,75 per year)

The insurance can be canceled every year, even if you have paid in advance. If you cancel earlier, you will receive a refund for the overpaid amount.
